    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">I bid 1-3, depends on the opponenets shadow, and hope I can go first. Cant bid more then that because of bad burden removal, all I have is Narya. Play Gandalf asap with his weapons and condition. Exert Gandalf to boost Arwen and Legolas (Narya and the Staff are great with their extra vitality), they are the primary fighters in the deck. Aragorn is only cannon fodder, dont be afraid to loose him when you face too many minions. Every1 except Gandalf have the Gandalf signet, so I can use Trust me as you Once Did with its full power. Intimidate saves my elves lives, because they dont have any armors, and they especially dont like Lurtz Battle Cry. Heal every turn with Elrond, or throw conditions back to opponents hand with Vilya.<br />
<br />
Shadow is uruk beatdown, nothing special about that. Troops are great, play 4 of them. Savagery punishes bigger fellowships, and Berserker punishes burdens. Saruman is great, maybe the best card from RotEL, all Uruks fierce means alot of wounds. Raiders work well together with Tower Assassins, especially with all the new allies from RotEL. A fierce strength 9 minion for 2 twilights is not so bad.<br />
<br />
<br />
Site choices:<br />
<br />
1: No other good sites for this deck<br />
2: No ARV, only play one hobbit<br />
3: Card drawing<br />
4: No roaming<br />
5: ...<br />
6: Great to double move from site 4 here<br />
7: Uruks dont like archery<br />
8: No ARV<br />
9: Cheap Uruks<br />
<br />
